      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Star filly ARRHYTHMIA (1) returns off a brilliant juvenile season that saw her win eight of nine starts including the Vicbred and Breeders Crown finals. Takes on older rivals but gets the ace draw and has been readied with two nice trials. NEW SHUFFLE (5) is in a purple patch of form having won his last two outings at Melton. Drops to a distance where he strikes at 50 per cent. Go well again. FOLLOWTHEACE (6) has trialled since he led and faded last start. Melton winner prior and has recorded a win and two placings from three tries at this distance. ALWAYS BE BLAKEY (9) draws on the back row again after winning from there last start and hasn't missed the top-three in four starts this time in. LE BELLE BIJOUX (4) has been coming from wider or second row draws and producing some decent efforts including a Melton win last month. Respect from a good draw.",
